Author: claude-opus47-app <claude-opus47-app@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 23 17:19:22 2026 +0800

    fix(bfs-adapter): DEC-V61-052 round 2d · endTime 1500 for stationary residual plateau (Codex round 1 #5)
    
    Codex round 1 LOW #5: "Convergence is stable, but metric stationarity is
    not yet demonstrated ... initial residuals still drop about 28-36% over
    the last 100 iterations." The 1000-iter fixture was stable (no divergence,
    positive turbulence scalars, continuity 7e-9) but Ux/Uy residuals were
    still on a 1e-5 → 1e-6 descent. Raising endTime to 1500 lets the residual
    drop to the plateau.
    
    Residual trajectory on the 1500-iter fixture:
      Ux: t=800 5.99e-5, t=1000 1.01e-5, t=1200 7.00e-6, t=1400 6.42e-6, t=1500 6.41e-6
      Late-window drift Δr/r at t=1400→1500: +0.1% per 100 iters → plateau.
    
    Xr/H stationarity:
      t=1000 (prior fixture): 5.642
      t=1500 (this fixture):  5.647  → drift +0.09% over 500 iters
    Both within 10% tolerance of Driver 1985 = 6.26. Xr is stationary.
    
    Preflight still exits 0 (GREEN all 6 checks):
      scalar contract: reattachment_length: actual=5.647  expected=6.26
      dev=-9.8% (tolerance ±10%)
    
    writeInterval kept at 100 (15 snapshots) — future stationarity gates can
    parse Xr at multiple time dirs if and when we plumb multi-snapshot reads
    through _parse_writeobjects_fields (out of scope for this round).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

